summary: This document is a signature page for an account application with J.P. Morgan, signed by Jeffrey Epstein. It outlines the terms and agreements for opening financial accounts and includes a certification regarding taxpayer identification and backup withholding. The document emphasizes the need for accurate information and the requirement for arbitration in case of disputes.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Jeffrey Epstein is identified as the President and the primary account holder signing the application for financial services with J.P. Morgan.

keyFacts: The document is a financial account application for J.P. Morgan.
Jeffrey Epstein is listed as the President and account holder.
The application includes a certification regarding taxpayer identification.
The document requires arbitration for any disputes arising from the account agreements.
Confidential treatment was requested by JPMorgan Chase for this document.
